  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nigerian Immigration Service - Training Strategy Implementation - Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over the past years, IOM has supported Nigerian Immigration Service (NIS) in developing and updating the NIS training strategy which aims to institutionalise the common training approach across the agency and boost its overall capacity in fulfilling its mandate defined in the 2015 Immigration Act. The first phase of the project successfully contributed to the implementation of the training strategy. Building on the outcome of Phase I and responding to the current pandemic, the proposed project aims to update the training curriculum and the learning management system, scale up the training programme to reach a larger number of NIS officers as well as enhance joint training efforts with the National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons (NAPTIP) with considerations to establishing COVID-19 control measures during trainings. This project primarily aims to enhance NIS and NAPTIP capacity to regularise processing of individuals passing international borders by applying legal, operational, and technical tools, and best practices in border management.</narrative>
  </description>
